<section version="5.0"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook http://www.docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd"
    xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mth="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
    xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <title>Create an external map layer</title>
    <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                    role="bold">Other</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">External map
                    layer</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click the add
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T112410+0200" comment="Do not refer to the FAB as an icon, according to MS Manual of Style." flag="done"?>button<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Name</emphasis> field, type the name of the external
                map layer.</para>
            <para>This is the name you'll see in the <emphasis role="bold">GIS</emphasis>
                app.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) In the <emphasis role="bold">Code</emphasis> field, assign a
                code.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Select a <emphasis role="bold">Map
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160928T121414+0200" comment="Should the different types be explained?"?>service<?oxy_comment_end?></emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Enter a <emphasis role="bold">URL</emphasis> to the map service.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) Enter the name of <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160928T114947+0200" comment="Before release: verify that UI item has changed to Source, not Attribution"?>the<?oxy_comment_end?>
                <emphasis role="bold">Source</emphasis> of the map service.</para>
            <para>When you use an external map service it is important to highlight where the data
                comes from.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Select a <emphasis role="bold">Placement</emphasis>: <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Bottom - basemap</emphasis>: places the external
                            map layer under the thematic map layers</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Top - overlay</emphasis>: places the external
                            map layer above the thematic map layers</para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) Select a <emphasis role="bold">Legend</emphasis>.</para>
            <tip>
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160526T104008+0200" comment="At next revision, ad x-ref." flag="done"?>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Add new</emphasis> to create legends that you're
                    missing. In the form that opens, create the legends you need. When you're done,
                    click <emphasis role="bold">Refresh values</emphasis>.</para>
                <?oxy_comment_end?>
            </tip>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) Enter a <emphasis role="bold">Legend image URL</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
</section>

